    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 4: Ube3A ubiquitinates small conductance potassium channels (SK) regulating its cell surface expression.\nFigure 5: Reversal of LTP impairment in Ube3A null (AS) mice by apamin, an SK2 channel blocker shows that Ube3A depletion leads to higher membrane expression of SK2 leading to LTP impairments.\nFigure 6: TBS failed to induce LTP in hippocampal slices from AS mice.\n\n19/6/2018 Pim\n- I find no data in the paper that places the SK2 endocytosis in the pre or postsynaptic compartment. The annotation of pre/postsynaptic endocytosis of the ion channel will not be made (and new terms implemented). Instead the annotation to 'modulation of chemical synaptic transmission (GO:0050804)' will be made to capture the effects on LTP.. Experimental description: M&M: Hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) mouse embryos, bred with UBE3Am/p+ female and male mice, as described previously (Qin et al., 2009).",
